# Course Conduct & Etiquette

## 8.1 The General Public
Our routes use public rights of way and national trails. You will encounter other users, including walkers, families, and dog owners. Please be courteous, polite, and patient. On narrow clifftop paths, come to a complete halt and yield the right of way to public path users where necessary.

---

## 8.2 The Countryside Code & Litter
* **Gate Etiquette:** Leave all trail gates exactly as you find them. Open and close agricultural gates gently to prevent damage to fencing.
* **Zero Litter Mandate:** Dropping wrappers, gel tabs, plastic bottles, or fruit peels along our trails is strictly forbidden. Retain all litter on your person and drop it into the bins provided at Checkpoints and Water Stations.
* **The 'One Piece' Campaign:** Join our rubbish challenge by picking up at least one piece of third-party litter from the trail during your race. We choose a spot prize winner at random from everyone who joins in and helps pick up litter on the trail.

---

## 8.3 Wildlife & Livestock
You will encounter livestock and wildlife along our coastal routes. Pass all animals at a slow walking pace, giving them as much space as possible. If approaching animals from behind, make clear vocal noise early to alert them and avoid startling them.

---

## 8.4 Headphones
These rules apply to all types of headphones (including bone-conduction models, wireless earbuds, and single-ear configurations) and apply to both ears. While headphones are permitted on open trail sectors, **you must completely remove them from your ears when:**
* You approach or pass any physical 'Caution' or safety sign.
* You are running across, alongside, or intersecting any public road.
* The footpath becomes narrow, technical, or restricted.
* You approach or pass any official Course Marshal or scanning staff.

Failure to remove headphones in these areas will result in an automatic time penalty.

---

## 8.5 Poles & Pacing
* **Running Poles:** The use of running or walking poles is fully permitted across all distance categories.
* **Pacing Restrictions:** Pacing—where an unregistered runner accompanies a participant on the course to assist them—is strictly prohibited and will result in immediate disqualification.

---

## 8.6 Running with Dogs
Running with quiet, well-behaved dogs is permitted, provided the animal stays securely on a short lead and under close control at all times. **Running with a dog automatically excludes you from official podium awards, overall prizes, or age-category classifications.**
